today explain linear regresions

Dependent Variable (DV): The outcome you want to predict (e.g., exam score).
Independent Variable(s) (IV): The predictors or inputs (e.g., hours studied).
Equation Form:
y = 𝛽0 + 𝛽1x + 𝜖
𝑦: predicted value
𝛽0: intercept
𝛽1: slope (effect of 𝑥 on 𝑦)
𝜖: error term
Simple Linear Regression: One independent variable.
Multiple Linear Regression: Two or more independent variables.
